The Director-General of the Nigerian Civil Aviation Authority, Captain Nuhu Musa has confirmed that the ongoing Anambra International Airport at Umueri, of Anambra East local government area of Anambra State, is true of international standard. Captain Musa made the confirmation on Wednesday while inspecting the airport project in the company of the state Governor, Willie Obiano and other senior officials of the Aviation Authority. Captain Musa, said with the level of compliance to standards, Anambra State has demonstrated that it means Aviation business. While adjudging the control tower as one of the best in the country, as well as other facilities, Captain Musa stressed that all the things needed in a standard airport are within the airport, pointing out that when completed, the airport will be a significant enabler of economic development in the area. Responding, Governor Obiano, who reiterated that the airport will be functional by April 2021, said that the govt has achieved a greater percentage of the project. Earlier, the State Commissioner for Works, Engineer Marcel Ifejiofor revealed that Governor Obiano has been supporting them since the project commenced one year ago, revealing that though they started with five contractors, eight contractors are now working on the project. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state. Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation af